source: Locke, Eleanor G. Sail Away 155 American Folk Songs to sing read and play Boosey & Hawkes, NY, 1981. 135.
Dallin, Leon and Lynn. Heritage Songster. Wm. C. Brown Co. Dubuque, Iowa, 1966. 109.
subject: love and courtship
notes: HS - Both the words and melody of this old English song exist in many versions.  Features they all have in common are a list of impossible tasks for the lovers to perform and the four seasonings--parsley, sage, rosemary, and thyme.
